- Rewrote AI config API endpoints (`backend/app/api/admin.py`) — replaced `response_model` + Pydantic `model_validate()` with manual `_ai_config_to_dict()` helper to ensure all fields (including `max_tokens`, `temperature`, masked `api_key`) are always present in responses
- Added `_mask_api_key()` helper for API key display masking
- Added `_sync_ai_model_configs()` in `backend/app/services/schema_sync.py` for database migration (ALTER TABLE to add new columns)
- Updated `backend/app/services/ai_service.py` — `_get_active_model_config()` now returns `max_tokens`/`temperature` from DB config; `call_ai_model()` uses these values instead of hardcoded defaults

### Admin Web

- Completely rewrote `admin-web/src/app/(admin)/ai-config/page.tsx` — changed from single-config form to full CRUD list management with Ant Design Table + Modal. Supports create, edit, delete, and test connection. All field names now match backend snake_case convention (`provider_name`, `base_url`, `model_name`, `api_key`, `max_tokens`, `temperature`, `is_active`). Added proper null safety for all data access.

### Deployment

